<html xmlns:t="http://tapestry.apache.org/schema/tapestry_5_1_0.xsd">
<head>
	<style type="text/css">
		body, td	{ font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;  font-size: smaller; }
	</style>
</head>
<body>
	<h1>AJAX Form</h1>
	
	This page demonstrates how Tapestry AJAX-enables a Form if you specifying the zone parameter of the Form.<br/><br/>
	
	<form t:type="form" t:zone="nameZone" style="background-color: eee; padding: 15px">
		First Name: <input t:type="TextField" t:id="firstName"/><br/>
		Last Name: <input t:type="TextField" t:id="lastName"/><br/><br/>
 
		<t:zone t:id="nameZone">
			Welcome ${name}.
		</t:zone><br/>

		Note that the following time field does not update because it's not in the zone:  ${time}
		<br/><br/>
		
		<input type="submit" value="Accept"/>
 	</form>
 	
	References: 
	<a href="http://tapestry.apache.org/tapestry5/tapestry-core/ref/org/apache/tapestry5/corelib/components/Form.html">Form</a>, 
	<a href="http://tapestry.apache.org/tapestry5/guide/ajax.html">Ajax</a>, 
	<a href="http://tapestry.apache.org/tapestry5/tapestry-core/ref/org/apache/tapestry5/corelib/components/Zone.html">Zone</a>,<br/><br/>

